PW is a HTTP/HTTPS daemon

 HTTPd features:
 - User-Certificate signin
 - uploads on PUT and POST (Container and HTML-<form> support) 
 - paging large-containers: summarization, Link headers, sorted-ranges, offsets/cursors
 - lazy indexing - GET stuff to index it in a traversible container
 - mostly conforming with http://linkeddata.github.io/SoLiD/

 MIME-types
 - input: Atom/RSS feeds, email, chatlogs, text-files, CSV, Markdown, highlighted-code
 - output: Atom/RSS, HTML, Turtle

SRC git clone https://github.com/hallwaykid/pw.git ||
    git clone http://repo.or.cz/w/www.git

PRE-INSTALL any missing dependencies

# voidlinux
$ xbps-install ruby ruby-devel libgit2-devel libxml2-devel libxslt-devel
$ gem install bundler

# debian
$ apt-get install ruby bundler libssl-dev libgit2-dev libxml2-dev libxslt1-dev pkg-config

INSTALL
$ cd pw/ruby     # enter srcdir
$ sh install     # symlink source to ruby $sitelibdir (in ~/ or system-wide depending on configuration)
$ bundle install # fetch required ruby libraries

USE
$ cd ..  # goto server-root. if elsewhere copy/link {css,js}/
$ ln conf/server/Procfile . # select Rack-engine
$ foreman start  # start HTTP/HTTPS daemons
#listen on 80/443 || # $ setcap cap_net_bind_service=+ep $(realpath `which ruby`)
# >1024 (behind apache/nginx/lighttpd)

repl$ irb -rww

OPTIONAL deps 
# mail
 getmail procmail msmtp mutt # see mail README
# code
 source-highlight python-Pygments

FRAMEWORK
 - customize: bind lambda to RDF-type 

CLEAN
$ rm -rf cache index
